From: Luiz Augusto von Dentz <luiz.von.dentz@intel.com>
Date: Wed, 20 Aug 2025 12:21:09 -0400
Subject: Bluetooth: hci_core: Print information of hcon on hci_low_sent
Patch-mainline: v6.18-rc1
Git-commit: 48a258b198c12685747beaf6392f2b68e6c542c2
References: jsc#PED-14261

This prints the information about the hcon on hci_low_sent to confirm
all connection are being processed.

Signed-off-by: Luiz Augusto von Dentz <luiz.von.dentz@intel.com>
Acked-by: Chun-Yi Lee <jlee@suse.com>
---
 net/bluetooth/hci_core.c |    4 ++++
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+)

--- a/net/bluetooth/hci_core.c
+++ b/net/bluetooth/hci_core.c
@@ -3435,6 +3435,10 @@ static struct hci_conn *hci_low_sent(str
 		    skb_queue_empty(&c->data_q))
 			continue;
 
+		bt_dev_dbg(hdev, "hcon %p state %s queued %d", c,
+			   state_to_string(c->state),
+			   skb_queue_len(&c->data_q));
+
 		if (c->state != BT_CONNECTED && c->state != BT_CONFIG)
 			continue;
 
